# HerCare App Implementation Plan (Phase 4)

Based on the `her_care_ui_flow.md` document, we have successfully created the main tab navigation and the first-time setup flow. For Phase 4, we will flesh out the remaining **Minimum Viable Screens** that currently don't have dedicated pages.

## Proposed Changes

We will create the following dedicated sub-pages and wire them into the application's router logic:

### 1. Settings (`src/pages/Settings.tsx` & `.css`)
A dedicated user profile and settings page accessible from the Home screen or via a new header icon.
- **Profile Info**: Name, Role
- **Shift Preferences**: Day/Night schedule defaults
- **Notifications**: Toggles for hydration and meal reminders

### 2. Add Meal (`src/pages/AddMeal.tsx` & `.css`)
A dedicated screen to add detailed meals.
- Accessed by clicking "Add Meal" from the `Meals` tab.
- Contains input fields for Meal Type, Time, Status, and Notes.

### 3. Note Editor (`src/pages/NoteEditor.tsx` & `.css`)
A dedicated text editor for composing thoughts.
- Accessed via the "Plus" button on the `Notes` tab.
- Contains an auto-expanding Title and Content text area.

### 4. Router Updates (`src/App.tsx`)
- Add new case statements in the `renderContent` block for `settings`, `add_meal`, and `note_editor`.
- Implement `onNavigate` callbacks on the parent tabs to route users to these new screens.

